    answer: "Hydrostatic pressure relief in Toronto typically costs $6,500-$16,000 depending on system complexity. Basic drainage solutions cost $6,500-$9,700, while comprehensive relief systems with wells and pumps range from $11,000-$16,000. Price varies by foundation depth and soil conditions."
  },
  {
    question: "How long does hydrostatic pressure relief installation take?",
    answer: "Most hydrostatic pressure relief projects take 3-7 days to complete. Exterior drainage systems require 3-5 days, while interior relief wells and comprehensive systems may take 5-7 days. Timeline depends on excavation requirements and weather conditions."
  },
  {
    question: "What are the benefits of hydrostatic pressure relief?",
    answer: "Pressure relief prevents foundation cracking, eliminates basement flooding, stops structural damage, protects home value, and provides peace of mind. Our systems include long-term warranties and prevent costly foundation repairs."
  },
  {
    question: "When do I need hydrostatic pressure relief?",
    answer: "Install pressure relief when you notice basement flooding, foundation cracks, walls bowing inward, wet basement floors, or high water table issues. Acting early prevents structural damage and is more cost-effective than emergency repairs."
